Naв‚‚COв‚ѓ + 2HCl в†’ 2NaCl + COв‚‚ + Hв‚‚O
Permanganate (MnOв‚„вЃ») Redox Titrations
Self-indicating вЂ” significant colour change from purple MnOв‚„вЃ» to colourless MnВІвЃғ.

MnOв‚„вЃ»(aq) + 8HвЃғ(aq) + 5FeВІвЃғ(aq) в†’ MnВІвЃғ(aq) + 4Hв‚‚O(l) + 5FeВівЃғ(aq)

End point (if MnOв‚„вЃ» in burette): first permanent pink colour (colourless в†’ purple).

Choosing the Correct Acid
Only use dilute sulfuric acid.

Insufficient Hв‚‚SOв‚„: Not acidic enough в†’ MnOв‚‚ produced instead of MnВІвЃғ; brown MnOв‚‚ masks colour change в†’ inaccurate (greater) volume
Ethanoic acid (weak): Cannot supply enough HвЃғ в†’ same problem as above
HCl: ClвЃ» oxidised to Clв‚‚ by MnOв‚„вЃ» (EВ° MnOв‚„вЃ»/MnВІвЃғ = +1.51 V > EВ° Clв‚‚/ClвЃ» = +1.36 V) в†’ greater volume + poisonous Clв‚‚
HNOв‚ѓ: Oxidising agent в†’ oxidises FeВІвЃғ to FeВівЃғ (EВ° NOв‚ѓвЃ»/HNOв‚‚ = +0.94 V > EВ° FeВівЃғ/FeВІвЃғ = +0.77 V) в†’ smaller volume
Iron Tablet Analysis вЂ” Detailed Procedure
Weigh accurately two ferrous sulfate tablets
Grind up with a little 1 M Hв‚‚SOв‚„ using pestle and mortar
Transfer paste into 100 cmВі volumetric flask via funnel; rinse with further small volumes of 1 M Hв‚‚SOв‚„
Make up to 100 cmВі with 1 M Hв‚‚SOв‚„; stopper and shake
Titrate 10.0 cmВі portions with 0.0050 M KMnOв‚„; end point = first permanent purple colour
