Detailed Method: Enthalpy of Solution of Anhydrous CuSOв‚„
Weigh 3.90вЂ“4.10 g anhydrous CuSOв‚„ in a dry weighing bottle (record precise mass)
Use volumetric pipette to place 25 cmВі deionised water in polystyrene cup; record temperature at t=0, then every minute, stirring continuously
At minute 4, add CuSOв‚„ rapidly; continue stirring but don't record temperature
Reweigh empty weighing bottle
From minute 5 to 15, stir and record temperature every minute
Plot temperature vs time; draw two best-fit lines; extrapolate both to minute 4
Determine О”T at minute 4
Calculate Q = 25 Г— 4.18 Г— О”T
Calculate О”H(solution) = Q / moles CuSOв‚„
Repeat with hydrated copper sulfate. Use the two О”H(solution) values to calculate О”H for hydration via Hess's law.

Flame Calorimetry (Enthalpies of Combustion)
Burn fuel в†’ heat water in metal cup. Measure: mass of spirit burner before/after, temperature change of water, volume of water.

Errors: Energy losses, incomplete combustion, incomplete energy transfer, evaporation of fuel after weighing, heat capacity of calorimeter not included, Hв‚‚O is gas not liquid (non-standard conditions).

